    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Egg Harbor City’s name comes from Captain Mey’s 17th‑century designation of the rivers as “Little Egg Harbor” and “Great Egg Harbor,” meaning “Harbor of Eggs.”",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
