      ],
      "source": "https://www.eggharborcity.org/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town was originally planned as a port on the Mullica River before the railroad shifted focus south.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.eggharborcity.org/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Egg Harbor City was conceived before the Civil War by German investors from Philadelphia, who planned the settlement shortly before 1861.",
